Compliance with their request, however, has been a labor ol love, and Ι trust it may prove not altogether labor lost.

The publication of the whole of the Letters, with an adequate commentary in English, has for some time seemed to me a very desirable work, -a work which Ι should like in future to attempt, should it not meantime be undertaken . by one better qualified for the task. Such an edition should be based upon a new reading of the manuscripts, as is conspicuously shown by a comparison of Keil’s edition with Professor Merrill's collation of the Codex Riccardianas in the American Journal of Plrilolopy‚ for December, 1895.
